<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FRONT STEER AXLE: EATON E1200I I-BEAM - STEERING KNUCKLE ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0200702" svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="10">
        <title>STEERING KNUCKLE ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Always replace both kingpin and bushings if either is faulty.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lightly lubricate the thrust bearing areas of the steering knuckle, the axle end, and the
                kingpin bore of the axle beam.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Pack dimples in bushing bores with grease.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position thrust bearing on lower knuckle bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200715">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200715" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200715" filename="../figg02/G0200715.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Position Thrust Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount thrust bearing and knuckle assembly on the axle beam.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pre-adjust knuckle vertical play by wedging the steering knuckle up and filling the gap at
                the top side of the knuckle with shim(s) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200716">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200716" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200716" filename="../figg02/G0200716.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Adjust Knuckle Vertical Play</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Shims are delicate and sharp. Extreme caution should be exercised while aligning shims so as
                        not to cut fingers or bend inside diameter of shims. Damage to shims during this entire
                        procedure requires disassembly and replacement of damaged parts.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install kingpin from the top with notch and draw key hole aligned. Hand start pin in bushing
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200717">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200717" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200717" filename="../figg02/G0200717.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Hand Start Pin</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Never shim on the bottom side of the beam.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install n in knuckle and axle beam. Tap kingpin in place using hammer and brass drift if
                necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200718">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200718" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200718" filename="../figg02/G0200718.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Tag Kingpin In Place</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Protect kingpins with a suitable material such as shim stock.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>At this point in reassembly, check knuckle vertical play and adjust if necessary.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Center steering components.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount dial indicator to flange and reference top of kingpin. Zero dial indicator (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200719">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200719" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200719" filename="../figg02/G0200719.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Dial Indicator</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Simulate axle loading with a jack and note dial indicator reading (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200720">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200720" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200720" filename="../figg02/G0200720.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Simulate Axle Loading</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Knuckle vertical play should be 0.002 to 0.012 inch (0.051 to 0.305mm). Add or remove shims
                as necessary to obtain correct end play.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When vertical play adjustment is correct, align draw key opening and pin flat alignment (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200721">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200721" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200721" filename="../figg02/G0200721.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Align Draw Key Opening</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new draw key.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1 id="hl0200703">
            <para count="1">Seat draw key with a hammer and punch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200722">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200722" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200722" filename="../figg02/G0200722.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Seat Draw Key</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install draw key nut and tighten to 30 to 45 ft-lbs. (41 to 61 N&#183;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200723">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200723" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200723" filename="../figg02/G0200723.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Draw Key Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Ensure draw key is fully seated by repeating
                <hotlnk xrefid="hl0200703">step 13</hotlnk>. Recheck draw key nut torque.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install gasket and knuckle kingpin caps. Tighten cap to 50 to 75 ft-lbs. (68 to 102 N&#183;m).</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Tighten nut to range minimum in steps 17 and 19 below, then tighten just enough to align
                        cotter pin hole.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach drag link to steering arm. Install and tighten to 165 to 230 ft-lbs. (224 to 312 N&#183;m).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install cotter pin.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not back off nuts to align cotter pin holes with slot in nut.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach tie rod end to tie rod arm on knuckle. Install nut and tighten to 120 to 160 ft-lbs.
                (163 to 217 N&#183;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200724">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200724" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200724" filename="../figg02/G0200724.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Figure</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install cotter pin.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not back off nuts to align cotter pin holes with slot in nut.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
